'''CurlFtpFS''' [[Article description::allows for [[mount|mounting]] an FTP folder as a regular directory to the local directory tree.]]

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

CurlFtpFS needs [[FUSE]] activated in the kernel:

{{KernelBox|title=Activating FUSE|1=
File systems --->
   <*> FUSE (Filesystem in Userspace) support 
}}

=== Emerge ===

Install {{Package|net-fs/curlftpfs}}:

{{Emerge|net-fs/curlftpfs}}

== Usage ==

=== As a regular user ===

First, create a mount point:

{{Cmd|mkdir ./ftp}}

==== Mounting ====

Then mount the necessary ''catalog'' from the ''server'' to this mount point:

{{Cmd|curlftpfs ftp://server/catalog/ ./ftp/ -o user{{=}}username:password,utf8}}

==== Unmounting ====

{{Cmd|fusermount -u ./ftp}}

